Task 4: Optimization Using PuLP

📄 Description

Formulated and solved a Linear Programming problem using PuLP to maximize profit in a bakery scenario.

📁 Files

optimization_model.ipynb

🧪 Problem

1 cake takes 2 hours, gives ₹200

1 bread takes 1 hour, gives ₹100

Maximum 40 hours available

🧪 Steps Performed

Defined decision variables: Cake, Bread

Created objective function: Maximize profit

Added constraint: Total hours ≤ 40

Solved using PuLP

🛠️ Libraries Used

pulp

✅ Output

Optimal number of cakes: 10
Optimal number of breads: 20
Maximum Profit: ₹4000


